This paper focuses on deep learning architectures and optimization techniques for medical image segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and optimization techniques such as stochastic gradient descent (SGD) and Adam also suggest the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the evaluation of different architectures and their computational requirements may also fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of medical imaging data may also suggest the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
